""Jedan narod, jedan kralj, jedna drzava"(Latin script)"@en

"The Kingdom of Yugoslavia (Kraljevina Jugoslavija, Serbian Cyrillic: ) was a state straddling the Western Balkans and Central Europe, that existed during the interwar period (19181939) and first half of World War II (19391943). It was formed in 1918 by the merger of the provisional State of Slovenes, Croats and Serbs (itself formed from territories of the former Austro-Hungarian Empire) with the formerly independent Kingdom of Serbia."@en
